<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC "-//Apache Software Foundation//DTD XDOC 1.0//EN" "http://maven.apache.org/dtd/xdoc_1_0.dtd">
<document>
  <properties>
    <title>How to install PSUtils library</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="How to install the Hippo Utilities modules">
      <subsection name="Maven 2 Forge Repository">
        <p>Add this repository to your root pom.xml (if not already present in a parent pom):</p>
        <source><![CDATA[
  <repository>
    <id>hippo-forge</id>
    <name>Hippo Forge maven 2 repository.</name>
    <url>http://maven.onehippo.com/maven2-forge/</url>
    <snapshots>
      <enabled>false</enabled>
    </snapshots>
    <releases>
      <updatePolicy>never</updatePolicy>
    </releases>
    <layout>default</layout>
  </repository>]]></source>
      </subsection>

      <subsection name="Installation of HST module">
          <p>Assuming that the version is managed in the parent pom, add this dependency to the pom.xml of your site module:</p>
          <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.utilities</groupId>
  <artifactId>hippo-utilities-hst</artifactId>
</dependency>]]></source>
          <p>The following artifact should be provided also: </p>
          <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>com.google.guava</groupId>
  <artifactId>guava</artifactId>
  <version>r06</version> <!-- or higher -->
</dependency>]]></source>

      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Installation of repository module">
          <p>Assuming that the version is managed in the parent pom, add this dependency to the pom.xml of the repository (content) module:</p>
          <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.utilities</groupId>
  <artifactId>hippo-utilities-repository</artifactId>
</dependency>]]></source>
          <p>If you are using the <a href="repository/scheduler-daemon.html">SchedulerDaemon</a>, also include a quartz dependency. Use the same quartz version as the repository already has,
            which is 1.8.4 in CMS 7.7. It is recommended to manage this version in the parent pom.</p>
          <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.quartz-scheduler</groupId>
  <artifactId>quartz</artifactId>
  <version>1.8.4</version>
</dependency>]]></source>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Installation of CMS module">
          <p>Assuming that the version is managed in the parent pom, add this dependency to the pom.xml of your CMS module:</p>
          <source><![CDATA[
<dependency>
  <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.utilities</groupId>
  <artifactId>hippo-utilities-cms</artifactId>
</dependency>]]></source>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
